# Local Workflow Rules

## Adversarial Review Loop
- Users direct the coder to implement a feature.
- The coder implements with TDD, verifies, commits, and hands off to reviewer.
- The reviewer critically analyzes the code, tests, design, and verification evidence.
- If changes are needed, the reviewer writes committed recommendations and hands off to coder.
- The coder reads the recommendations, makes the changes, verifies, commits, and hands off to reviewer again.
- Repeat until the reviewer is satisfied.
- When satisfied, the reviewer records approval in the repo, commits it, reports satisfaction, and stops without handing off another work item.

## Review Artifacts
- Reviewer recommendations live under `review/recommendations.md`.
- Reviewer approval lives under `review/approval.md`.
- Keep review artifacts concise, specific, and actionable.
